The ClassIds are used to identify Object child classes through the Object::Is virtual method.

detaileddescription.para: Each Object child class has to have its own id and has to override the GetClassId() method. Base classes (e.g., LayerElement) that are never instanciated have boundary ids used for checking if an Object is child of a base class. See for example Object::IsLayerElement.
